{"url": "https://www.freelancer.in/projects/market-analysis/betfair-api-betting-signal-engine.html", "title": "Betfair API Betting Signal Engine Development", "budget": "Budget \u00a3250 \u2013 750 GBP", "parsed_budget": {"min": "250", "max": "750", "currency_symbol": "\u00a3", "currency": "GBP", "per_hour": false}, "description": "Betting Signal Developer \u2013 Betfair API + Market Simulation System\n\nProject Objective\nBuild a live, automated betting signal engine that:\n- Connects directly to Betfair Exchange live markets\n- Streams real-time price, volume, and graph data\n- Calculates custom BTL Ratios, Confidence Scores, Lay Pressure, and other market indicators\n- Logs market behavior and outcomes to support daily simulations and scoring logic\n- Flags back/lay signals, market misdirection events, and false negatives\n\nTech Stack & Skills Required\n- Strong experience with Betfair Exchange API (Streaming + Historical if possible)\n- Proficient in Python (preferred) or Node.js, with good understanding of async handling\n- Ability to handle live data streams, manage API rate limits, and log efficiently\n- Experience with data pipelines or betting signal models a big bonus\n- Familiarity with market metrics like BTL ratio, liquidity shifts, late drifters, compression patterns, etc.\n- Optional: GUI/dashboard experience for displaying signal orders (e.g. Streamlit, Flask)\n\nCore Tasks\n1. Live Market Feed\n- Pull current prices, back/lay depth, matched money\n- Extract data for top 3 runners in all UK/IRE races pre-off\n\n2. Signal Engine\n- Calculate custom BTL ratios and Confidence Scores based on defined logic\n- Monitor market pressure and flag late surges/drifts\n\n3. Simulation Support\n- Log all inputs (market, time, final price)\n- Tag races with signals: bullish, bearish, neutral-stable, misdirection, etc.\n- Store outcomes for comparison to live race results\n\n4. Optional Add-ons\n- Alert system for flagged lays/back bets\n- Historical data backfill