{"url": "https://www.freelancer.in/projects/api/mvp-developer-for-lightweight-tool.html", "title": "MVP Developer for Lightweight AI Tool (OpenAI API)", "budget": "Budget $750 \u2013 1,500 USD\nRECRUITER", "parsed_budget": {"min": "750", "max": "1500", "currency_symbol": "$", "currency": "USD", "per_hour": false}, "description": "We're building a lean MVP for an AI-powered product and are looking for a technical partner/freelancer to bring the backend logic to life. The front end is already built using Lovable (a no-code builder similar to Webflow/Framer). We now need to connect it to an LLM backend via OpenAI's API and set up data flow using Make.com (formerly Integromat).\n\nYou won't need to train any models \u2014 just work with API requests and create clean, reliable logic that transforms user inputs into smart outputs.\n\nWhat You'll Do:\nConnect front-end prompt form (Lovable) to OpenAI API using Make.com\n\nSet up a Make.com scenario with a POST request to OpenAI\u2019s chat/completions endpoint\n\nFormat system/user messages properly to achieve desired responses\n\nDisplay AI responses on the Lovable site (returned back to the frontend cleanly)\n\nOptional: Set up Supabase (or similar) for storing prompt history or user data\n\nOptional: Help with light error handling (e.g., empty inputs, failovers, slow responses)", "skills": ["API", "Backend Development", "API", "Backend Development", "CSS", "Frontend Development", "HTML"], "ClientRating": 0.0, "ClientReviews": 0, "timestamp": "2025-07-28T15:18:42.423408+00:00"}
{"url": "https://www.freelancer.in/projects/webrtc/fix-call-connection-failures-app.html", "title": "Fix Call Connection Failures in App", "budget": "Budget $250 \u2013 750 USD", "parsed_budget": {"min": "250", "max": "750", "currency_symbol": "$", "currency": "USD", "per_hour": false}, "description": "can you help me with my app where users can make voice and video calls using WebRTC. Signaling is done with Socket.IO. We use ICE servers from Twilio, Xirsys, and a self-hosted Coturn server on DigitalOcean with TLS The problem is that calls often fail. Signaling works, but media doesn\u2019t. One or both users can\u2019t see or hear each other. This happens more frequently when users are in different countries, behind strict NATs, or using VPNs. We need a WebRTC expert to investigate and fix the root cause of these ICE negotiation failures. The goal is to make sure calls always connect, no matter the device, network, or location. This includes Android to Android, iOS to iOS, and Android to iOS combinations. You must optimize our Coturn setup, improve ICE server usage, and optionally implement automatic fallback logic if a connection fails. You should also explain the solution so we can maintain it. Tech stack: Ionic with Angular frontend, Node.js with Express backend, WebRTC for media, Socket.IO for signaling, and ICE servers from Coturn, Twilio, and Xirsys. Final goal: 100% reliable voice and video calls under all conditions.", "skills": ["Android", "Angular", "Android", "Angular", "Linux", "Mobile App Development", "Node.js"], "ClientRating": 5.0, "ClientReviews": 1, "timestamp": "2025-07-28T15:18:54.254498+00:00"}
